st=[[Lena Login|Login]]|year=1890|publisher=Languages Dept|location=Punjab}} \n* {{cite book|first=Kenneth J.|last=Mears|title=The Tower of London: 900 Years of English History|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=D_kgAAAAMAAJ|year=1988|publisher=Phaidon|isbn=978-0-7148-2527-4}}\n* {{cite book|first1=Kenneth J.|last1=Mears|first2=Simon|last2=Thurley|first3=Claire|last3=Murphy|title=The Crown Jewels|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=r1GJnAEACAAJ|year=1994|publisher=Historic Royal Palaces|asin=B000HHY1ZQ}}\n<!-- R to Y -->\n* {{cite book|first=P. N.|last=Rastogi|title=Ethnic Tensions in Indian Society: Explanation, Prediction, Monitoring and Control|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=xBOlsFQH-toC|year=1986|publisher=Mittal Publications|isbn=978-9-997-38489-8}}\n* {{cite book|first=Tessa|last=Rose|title=The Coronation Ceremony and the Crown Jewels|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=bSUTAQAAIAAJ|year=1992|publisher=HM Stationery Office|isbn=978-0-117-01361-2}}\n* {{cite book|first=Henry George|last=Smith|title=Gems and Precious Stones|url=https://archive.org/details/gemspreciousston00smitrich|year=1896|publisher=Charles Potter}}\n* {{cite book|first1=Edwin William|last1=Streeter|first2=Joseph|last2=Hatten|title=The Great Diamonds of the World|url=https://archive.org/details/greatdiamondsofw00stre|year=1882|publisher=G. Bell & Sons}}\n* {{cite journal|last1=Sucher|first1=Scott D.|last2=Carriere|first2=Dale P.|year=2008|title=The Use of Laser and X-ray Scanning to Create a Model of the Historic Koh-i-Noor Diamond|journal=Gems & Gemology|volume=44|issue=2|pages=124\u2013141|doi=10.5741/GEMS.44.2.124}}\n* {{cite journal|journal=New Zealand Journal of History|volume=15|issue=1|issn=0028-8322|date=April 1981|first=Nicholas|last=Tarling|authorlink=Nicholas Tarling|publisher=University of Auckland|url=http://www.nzjh.auckland.ac.nz/docs/1981/NZJH_15_1_03.pdf|title=The Wars of British Succession}}\n* {{cite journal |first=Dena K.|last=Tarshis |year=2000 |title=The Koh-i-Noor Diamond and its Glass Replica at the Crystal Palace Exhibition |jstor=24191006 |journal=Journal of Glass Studies |publisher=Corning Museum of Glass |volume=42 |pages=133\u2013143 |issn=0075-4250 }}\n* {{cite journal |last=Young |first=Paul |year=2007 |title=\"Carbon, Mere Carbon\": The Kohinoor, the Crystal Palace, and the Mission to Make Sense of British India |url= |journal=Nineteenth-Century Contexts |volume=29 |issue=4 |pages=343\u2013358 |doi=10.1080/08905490701768089 }}\n* {{cite book|first1=Sir George|last1=Younghusband|first2=Cyril|last2=Davenport|title=The Crown Jewels of England|url=https://archive.org/details/TheCrownJewelsOfEngland|year=1919|publisher=Cassell & Co.|asin=B00086FM86}}\n{{Refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Koh-i-Noor Diamond}}\n* {{Wikisource-inline|links=[[s:The Folk-Lore Journal/Volume 4/A Story of the Koh-i-N\u00fbr|the Koh-i-Noor]]}}\n\n{{Crown Jewels of the United Kingdom}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Koh-I-Noor}}\n[[Category:Crown Jewels of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Jewels of the Mughal Empire]]\n[[Category:Diamonds originating in India]]\n[[Category:History of India]]\n[[Category:History of Andhra Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Sikh Empire]]\n[[Category:1739 in Asia]]\n[[Category:Persian words and phrases]]\n[[Category:Golconda diamonds]]\n", "name_user": "24.71.233.102", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Koh-i-Noor"}
{"title_page": "Matthew Smithard", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name     = Matthew Smithard\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Matthew Smithard\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1976|6|13|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Leeds]], England\n| height         = \n| position       = [[Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1    = 1992\u20131996\n| youthclubs1    = [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n| years1         = 1996\u20131997\n| clubs1         = [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]\n| caps1          = 1\n| goals1         = 0\n| years2         = 1997\u20131999\n| clubs2         = [[Farsley Celtic A.F.C.|Farsley Celtic]]\n| caps2          = ?\n| goals2         = ?\n| years3         = 1999\u20132002\n| clubs3         = [[Ossett Town F.C.|Ossett Town]]\n| caps3          = ?\n| goals3         = ?\n| years4         = 2002\u20132004\n| clubs4         = [[Farsley Celtic A.F.C.|Farsley Celtic]]\n| caps4          = ?\n| goals4         = ?\n| years5         = 2004\u20132006\n| clubs5         = [[Guiseley A.F.C.|Guiseley]]\n| caps5          = ?\n| goals5         = ?\n| totalcaps      = ?\n| totalgoals     = ?\n}}\n'''Matthew Smithard''' (born 13 June 1976) is an English former professional [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[midfielder]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Leeds]], Smithard began his career with the youth team of hometown club [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]], winning the [[FA Youth Cup Finals of the 1990s#1992/93: Leeds United v. Manchester United (2-0 and 2-1, 4-1 Aggregate)|1993 FA Youth Cup]].<ref name=\"NLD\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nonleaguedaily.com/teams/players.php?pid=2995 |title=Player profile |accessdate=4 June 2010 |publisher=NonLeagueDaily.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120929161726/http://www.nonleaguedaily.com/teams/players.php?pid=2995 |url-status=dead |archivedate=29 September 2012 }}</ref> However, he never played a first-team game for the club, and Smithard began his professional career during the 1996\u201397 season with [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]], making one appearance for them in [[the Football League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/bradfordcity/bradfordcity.html|title=BRADFORD CITY : 1946/47 - 2008/09|accessdate=4 June 2010|publisher=Post War English & Scottish Football League A - Z Player's Transfer Database}}</ref> After dropping down to non-League football due to injury,<ref name = \"NLD\"/> Smithard played with a number of teams including [[Farsley Celtic A.F.C.|Farsley Celtic]], [[Ossett Town F.C.|Ossett Town]] and [[Guiseley A.F.C.|Guiseley]].<ref name = \"NLD\"/><ref>http://www.thetelegraphandargus.co.uk/news/8083864.Parsley_signs_up_Lee_as_Guiseley_move_into_the_play_off_places/?ref=rl</ref>\n\n==References==\n;General\n*{{soccerbase|7449|Matthew Smithard}}\n\n;Specific\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Smithard, Matthew}}\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Leeds]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Leeds United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bradford City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Farsley Celtic A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Ossett Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Guiseley A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n\n\n{{England-footy-midfielder-1970s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name     = Matthew Smithard\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Matthew Smithard\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1976|6|13|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Leeds]], England\n| height         = {{height|ft=5|in=10}}\n| position       = [[Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1    = 1992\u20131996\n| youthclubs1    = [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n| years1         = 1996\u20131997\n| clubs1         = [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]\n| caps1          = 1\n| goals1         = 0\n| years2         = 1997\u20131999\n| clubs2         = [[Farsley Celtic A.F.C.|Farsley Celtic]]\n| caps2          = ?\n| goals2         = ?\n| years3         = 1999\u20132002\n| clubs3         = [[Ossett Town F.C.|Ossett Town]]\n| caps3          = ?\n| goals3         = ?\n| years4         = 2002\u20132004\n| clubs4         = [[Farsley Celtic A.F.C.|Farsley Celtic]]\n| caps4          = ?\n| goals4         = ?\n| years5         = 2004\u20132006\n| clubs5         = [[Guiseley A.F.C.|Guiseley]]\n| caps5          = ?\n| goals5         = ?\n| totalcaps      = ?\n| totalgoals     = ?\n}}\n'''Matthew Smithard''' (born 13 June 1976) is an English former professional [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[midfielder]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Leeds]], Smithard began his career with the youth team of hometown club [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]], winning the [[FA Youth Cup Finals of the 1990s#1992/93: Leeds United v. Manchester United (2-0 and 2-1, 4-1 Aggregate)|1993 FA Youth Cup]].<ref name=\"NLD\">{{cite web|url=http://www.nonleaguedaily.com/teams/players.php?pid=2995 |title=Player profile |accessdate=4 June 2010 |publisher=NonLeagueDaily.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120929161726/http://www.nonleaguedaily.com/teams/players.php?pid=2995 |url-status=dead |archivedate=29 September 2012 }}</ref> However, he never played a first-team game for the club, and Smithard began his professional career during the 1996-97 season with [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]], making one appearance for them in [[the Football League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/bradfordcity/bradfordcity.html|title=BRADFORD CITY : 1946/47 - 2008/09|accessdate=4 June 2010|publisher=Post War English & Scottish Football League A - Z Player's Transfer Database}}</ref> After dropping down to non-League football due to injury,<ref name = \"NLD\"/> Smithard played with a 