atches played}}!!{{abbr|W|Matches won}}!!{{abbr|D|Matches drawn}}!!{{abbr|L|Matches lost}}!!{{abbr|Win %|Win percentage}}\n|-\n|align=left|[[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] (caretaker)\n|align=left|24 April 2017\n|align=left|26 May 2017\n{{WDL|2|1|0|1|decimals=1}}\n|<ref name=\"HartlepoolStart\"/><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/40063109 |title=Craig Harrison: Hartlepool appoint The New Saints boss as manager |publisher=BBC Sport |date=26 May 2017 |accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Hartlepool: Results/matches: 2016/17 |url=http://www.soccerbase.com/teams/team.sd?team_id=1190&teamTabs=results&season_id=149 |work=Soccerbase |publisher=Centurycomm |accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|align=left|[[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]]\n|align=left|21 February 2018\n|align=left|28 November 2018\n{{WDL|38|13|12|13|decimals=1}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46378253|title=Matthew Bates: Hartlepool United sack manager after nine months in charge\n|date=27 November 2018|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=27 November 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n!colspan=3|Total\n{{WDLtot|40|14|12|14|decimals=1}}\n!\u2014\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n===As a player===\n'''Middlesbrough'''\n*[[FA Youth Cup]]: 2003\u201304<ref name=\"Hugman2010/11\"/>\n* [[UEFA Europa League|UEFA Cup]] Runner-up: [[2006 UEFA Cup Final|2005\u201306]]\n\n===As a manager===\n'''Awards'''\n*March 2018 [[National League (division)|National League]] Manager of the Month<ref name=\"Bates Wins Manager Of The Month\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Matthew Bates}}\n*[https://www.hartlepoolunited.co.uk/teams/first-team/defender/matthew-bates/ Matthew Bates profile]{{Dead link|date=December 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} at the Hartlepool United F.C. website\n*{{Soccerbase}}\n\n{{Hartlepool United F.C. managers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bates, Matthew}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Stockton-on-Tees]]\n[[Category:Footballers from County Durham]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:England youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Middlesbrough F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Darlington F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Ipswich Town F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Norwich City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bristol City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bradford City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Hartlepool United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Premier League players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:English football managers]]\n[[Category:Hartlepool United F.C. managers]]\n[[Category:English Football League managers]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) managers]]\n[[Category:Hartlepool United F.C. non-playing staff]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use British English|date=July 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|          name      = Matthew Bates\n|               image = Matthew Bates 15-08-2015 1.jpg\n|          image_size = 200\n|             caption = Bates playing for [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] in 2015\n|            fullname = Matthew David Bates<ref name=\"Hugman2010/11\">{{cite book |editor-first=Barry J. |editor-last=Hugman |title=The PFA Footballers' Who's Who 2009\u201310 |year=2009 |publisher=Mainstream Publishing |location=Edinburgh |isbn=978-1-84596-474-0 |page=37}}</ref>\n|         birth_date = {{birth date and age|1986|12|10|df=y}}<ref name=\"Hugman2010/11\"/>\n| birth_place = [[Stockton-on-Tees]], England\n|              height = {{height|ft=5|in=10}}<ref name=\"Hugman2010/11\"/>\n|            position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n|\n|          clubnumber = \n|         youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}\u20132004\n|         youthclubs1 = [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]]\n|              years1 = 2004\u20132012\n|              years2 = 2005\n|              years3 = 2006\n|              years4 = 2008\n|              years5 = 2012\u20132013\n|              years6 = 2013\u20132014\n|              years7 = 2014\u20132018\n|              clubs1 = [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]]\n|              clubs2 = \u2192 [[Darlington F.C.|Darlington]] (loan)\n|              clubs3 = \u2192 [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]] (loan)\n|              clubs4 = \u2192 [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] (loan)\n|              clubs5 = [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]]\n|              clubs6 = [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]\n|              clubs7 = [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]]\n|               caps1 = 104\n|              goals1 = 6\n|               caps2 = 4\n|              goals2 = 0\n|               caps3 = 2\n|              goals3 = 0\n|               caps4 = 3\n|              goals4 = 0\n|               caps5 = 13\n|              goals5 = 0\n|               caps6 = 22\n|              goals6 = 0\n|               caps7 = 77\n|              goals7 = 2\n<!--|      nationalyears1 = 2004\n|       nationalteam1 = [[England national under-18 football team|England U18]]\n|       nationalcaps1 = 2\n|      nationalgoals1 = 0\n|      nationalyears2 = 2004\u20132005\n|       nationalteam2 = [[England national under-19 football team|England U19]]\n|       nationalcaps2 = 3\n|      nationalgoals2 = 0-->\n|         club-update = 15:24, 17 June 2017 (UTC)\n|  manageryears1 = 2017\n|  managerclubs1 = [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] (caretaker)\n|  manageryears2 = 2018\n|  managerclubs2 = [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]]\n}}\n'''Matthew David Bates''' (born 10 December 1986) is an English former football manager and former professional [[Association football|footballer]], as well as holding a [[UEFA B Licence|UEFA B coaching licence]].\n\nBates played for [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]], [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]], [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]], [[Darlington F.C.|Darlington]], [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]], [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] and [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Middlesbrough===\nBorn in [[Stockton-on-Tees]], County Durham,<ref name=\"Hugman2010/11\"/> Bates began playing at [[Manchester United]]'s centre of excellence in [[Birtley, Tyne and Wear|Birtley]] since the age of nine. Several years later, the centre was closed down and he was taken in by his hometown club [[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]]. After tasting [[FA Youth Cup]] success in 2003\u201304, he was promoted to the first team and made his debut on 6 December 2004, coming on as an injury time replacement for [[Jimmy Floyd Hasselbaink]] in a 3\u20132 win over [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]]. After a successful loan spell at [[Darlington F.C.|Darlington]], he made a breakthrough, making 28 appearances and played alongside former manager [[Gareth Southgate]] in central defence.<ref>{{cite news|title=Saturday Spotlight Survival would complete Bates' recovery|url=http://www.darlingtonandstocktontimes.co.uk/archive/2009/04/25/Sport:+Football+(Middlesbrough+News)/4319793.Saturday_Spotlight/|newspaper=Darlington & Stockton Times |date=25 April 2009}}</ref>\n\nBates had been tipped by some to be Southgate's successor but an injury while on loan at [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich]] in November 2006 prematurely ended his 2006\u201307 season. He was seriously injured in his second game, tearing his [[cruciate ligament]] and partially tearing his [[medial collateral ligament]], and returned to Boro.<ref>[http://www.mfc.premiumtv.co.uk/page/News/NewsDetail/0,,1~934131,00.html \"Cruel blow for Matthew\"]. Middlesbourgh F.C. {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080214215405/http://www.mfc.premiumtv.co.uk/page/News/NewsDetail/0%2C%2C1~934131%2C00.html |date=14 February 2008}}</ref> After recovering in January 2008, Bates moved on loan to [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] for two months. He later returned to Middlesbrough after suffering from another knee injury which has resulted in him needing an operation for the third time in just 18 months.<ref>[http://www.canaries.premiumtv.co.uk/page/NewsDetails/0,,10355~1229256,00.html \"City sign Bates on loan\"]. Norwich City F.C. 30 January 2008. {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080201061016/http://www.canaries.premiumtv.co.uk/page/NewsDetails/0%2C%2C10355~1229256%2C00.html |date=1 February 2008 }}</ref> He scored his first league goal for Middlesbrough in a crucial 3\u20131 win over relegation rivals Hull on 11 April 2009.<ref>{{cite news\n|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_prem/7978843.stm\n|title=Middlesbrough 3\u20131 Hull\n|publisher=BBC Sport\n|date=11 April 2009 |accessdate=31 August 2009}}</ref>\n\nFollowing Middlesbrough's relegation from the [[Premier League]] in the [[Middlesbrough F.C. season 2008\u201309|2008\u201309 season]], rumours arose regarding his future with them. However, despite a number of Premier League clubs being interested, he opted to stay at Middlesbrough signed a new three-year deal at the Riverside outfit.<ref>[http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11680_5395365,00.html \"Bates pens Boro deal: Middlesbrough ace signs on for three more years\"]. Sky Sports. 22 June 2009.</ref>\n\nOn 25 July, Bates suffered the fourth serious knee injury of his career and could be sidelined for the rest of the year.<ref>Richardson, Andy (27 July 2009). [http://www.thenorthernecho.co.uk/sport/4513730.Bates_knee_injury_is_huge_blow_for_Boro/ \"Bates knee injury is huge blow for Boro\"]. ''The Northern Echo''. Darlington.</ref> He went for surgery in September and is confirmed to be out for the entire season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bates heads to the USA in latest fightback|url=http://www.darlingtonandstocktontimes.co.uk/archive/2009/11/24/Sport%3A+Football+%28Middlesbrough+News%29/4756270.Bates_heads_to_USA_in_latest_fightback/|newspaper=Darlington & Stockton Times |date=24 November 2009}}</ref>\n\nThe 2010/11 season saw Bates as a regular in the Boro line-up. He got his first goal of the season against [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]] in a 2\u20132 draw. Under new Boro manager [[Tony Mowbray]] Bates was named new captain. He scored the only goal in a 1\u20131 draw with [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]]. His third and final goal of the season came when he returned to the side after injury, playing in midfield, against [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]]. He was rewarded with a great start to the 2011/12 season by winning Player of the Month. On 27 March 2012, Bates suffered a fifth serious knee injury which ruled him out for a period of 6 months.\n\n===Bristol City===\nIn November 2012, Bates signed for Championship side [[Bristol City F.C.|Bristol City]] on a short-term deal until January 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=Matthew Bates signs short-term Bristol City contract|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/20377530|publisher=BBC Sport|date=17 November 2012}}</ref> He made his debut on 17 November in a 1\u20131 draw away to Blackpool, conceding a penalty in the 90th minute for handball, which [[Tom Ince]] converted.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/20278348 \"Bristol City 1\u20131 Blackpool\"] BBC Sport. 17 November 2012. Retrieved 19 October 2013.</ref> On 8 May 2013, Bates was released by City.\n\n===Bradford City===\nOn 13 October 2013, Bates signed a 3-month deal with [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]].<ref>[http://www.thetelegraphandargus.co.uk/sport/sportbcfc/10735620.Bates_signs_for_Bradford_City/ Bates signs for Bradford City (From )<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> On 15 January 2014, Bates signed a new deal with Bradford City until the end of the season.<ref>[http://www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk/news/article/bates-signs-new-deal-1296549.aspx Bates signs new deal<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>\n\n===Hartlepool United===\nBates joined [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] in June 2014.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/28003195 |title=Matthew Bates: Hartlepool sign ex-Middlesbrough defender |publisher=BBC Sport |date=24 June 2017 |accessdate=24 April 2017 }}</ref> Bates' playing stint with Hartlepool was ravaged by injuries with the defender making 77 league appearances in four years with the club.\n\n==International career==\nBates was [[Cap (sport)|capped]] by England at youth level.<ref name=\"Hugman2010/11\"/>\n\n==Management career==\nOn 24 April 2017, following the dismissal of [[Dave Jones (footballer, born 1956)|Dave Jones]], Bates was appointed caretaker manager of Hartlepool United for the final two matches of the [[2016\u201317 Hartlepool United F.C. season|2016\u201317 season]].<ref name=\"HartlepoolStart\">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39692440 |title=Dave Jones: Hartlepool United part company with manager |publisher=BBC Sport |date=24 April 2017 |accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref> Hartlepool won 2-1 in dramatic fashion on the final day of the season against [[Doncaster Rovers F.C.|Doncaster Rovers]] but this result wasn't enough, as a late [[Newport County A.F.C.|Newport County]] goal saw Hartlepool relegated from the Football League for the first time in their history.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hartlepool United 2-1 Doncaster Rovers - BBC Sport|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39753913|work=BBC Sport|date=6 May 2017}}</ref>\n\nWhen [[Craig Harrison (footballer)|Craig Harrison]] was appointed as Hartlepool's first-team manager in May 2017, Bates moved into a coaching role with the club's U21s side.\n\nOn 21 February 2018, Bates took charge of Hartlepool again following the dismissal of [[Craig Harrison (footballer)|Craig Harrison]].<ref name=\"HartlepoolCaretaker\">{{cite news |url=https://www.gazettelive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/craig-harrison-sacked-hartlepool-manager-14319271 |title=Craig Harrison sacked as Hartlepool manager as Paul Jenkins and Matthew Bates take temporary charge |publisher=GazetteLive |date=21 February 2018 |accessdate=4 May 2018}}</ref> Bates lost his first two games in charge as caretaker manager but managed to turn around the club's poor form and a crucial three-game win streak against [[Barrow A.F.C.|Barrow]], [[Bromley F.C.|Bromley]] and [[Maidstone United F.C.|Maidstone United]] led to him winning the Manager of the Month award for March 2018.<ref name=\"Bates Wins Manager Of The Month\">{{cite web|url=https://www.hartlepoolunited.co.uk/news/2018/april/090418-hartlepool-united-boss-matthew-bates-named-national-league-manager-of-month-for-march-2018/|title=Bates Wins Manager Of The Month|publisher=Hartlepool United FC|access-date=27 June 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627144352/https://www.hartlepoolunited.co.uk/news/2018/april/090418-hartlepool-united-boss-matthew-bates-named-national-league-manager-of-month-for-march-2018/|archive-date=27 June 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nAfter keeping Hartlepool in the division, Bates was appointed as permanent first-team manager in May 2018.<ref name=\"HartlepoolManager\">{{cite news |url=https://www.hartlepoolunited.co.uk/news/2018/may/040518-hartlepool-united-appoint-matthew-bates-as-the-new-first-team-manager/ |title=Matthew Bates Appointed As New Manager |publisher=Hartlepool United FC |date=4 May 2018 |accessdate=4 May 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180627202735/https://www.hartlepoolunited.co.uk/news/2018/may/040518-hartlepool-united-appoint-matthew-bates-as-the-new-first-team-manager/ |archive-date=27 June 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nAfter six successive league defeats, Bates was sacked as Hartlepool manager in November 2018.<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/46378253]</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nBates started dating [[Chanelle Hayes]] in 2009, though they split in 2010. She is the mother of Blakely Hayes-Bates, born July 2010.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-1256825/Newly-single-Chanelle-Hayes-cradles-stomach-looks-forward-motherhood.html|title=Newly single Chanelle Hayes cradles her stomach as she looks forward to motherhood|date=10 March 2010|newspaper=Daily Mail |location=London |accessdate=10 March 2010}}{{Unreliable source?|date=June 2017}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|match played 6 May 2017}}\n\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|[[FA Cup]]\n!colspan=2|[[EFL Cup|League Cup]]\n!colspan=2|Other\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=10|[[Middlesbrough F.C.|Middlesbrough]]\n|[[2003\u201304 Middlesbrough F.C. season|2003\u201304]]<ref name=\"soccerbase2003\">{{soccerbase season|38188|2003|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref>\n|[[Premier League]]\n|0||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||0||0\n|-\n|[[2004\u201305 Middlesbrough F.C. season|2004\u201305]]<ref name=\"soccerbase2004\">{{soccerbase season|38188|2004|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|2||0||0||0||0||0||0||0||2||0\n|-\n|[[2005\u201306 Middlesbrough F.C. season|2005\u201306]]<ref>{{soccerbase season|38188|2005|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|16||0||4||0||3||0||5{{efn|Appearances in [[2005\u201306 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]]}}||0||28||0\n|-\n|[[2006\u201307 Middlesbrough F.C. season|2006\u201307]]<ref name=\"soccerbase2006\">{{soccerbase season|38188|2006|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|1||0||0||0||1||0||colspan=2|\u2014||2||0\n|-\n|[[2007\u201308 Middlesbrough F.C. season|2007\u201308]]<ref name=\"soccerbase2007\">{{soccerbase season|38188|2007|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|0||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||0||0\n|-\n|[[2008\u201309 Middlesbrough F.C. season|2008\u201309]]<ref>{{soccerbase season|38188|2008|accessdate=17 June 2017}}</ref>\n|Premier League\n|17||1||3||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||20||1\n|-\n|[[2009\u201310 Middlesbrough F.C. 