{"title_page": "Matt Palmer (footballer)", "text_new": "{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Matt Palmer\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Matthew Thomas Palmer<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.football-league.co.uk/staticFiles/4e/bd/0,,10794~179534,00.pdf |title=Professional retain list & free transfers: 2012/13 |publisher=The Football League |format=PDF |page=57 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140802074454/http://www.football-league.co.uk/staticFiles/4e/bd/0%2C%2C10794~179534%2C00.pdf |archivedate=2 August 2014 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1995|2|27|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/matthew-palmer/257972/ |title=M. Palmer: Summary |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Derby]], England\n| height = {{convert|1.79|m|order=flip}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.themillers.co.uk/teams/first-team/midfielder/matthew-palmer/ |title=Matthew Palmer |publisher=Rotherham United F.C. |accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n| position = [[Midfielder]]<ref>{{Hugman|24871|accessdate=1 August 2018}}</ref>\n| currentclub = [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]]\n| clubnumber = 8\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]]\n| youthyears2 = {{0|000}}\u20132012\n| youthclubs2 = [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]]\n| years1 = 2012\u20132018\n| clubs1 = [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]]\n| caps1 = 136\n| goals1 = 6\n| years2 = 2016\n| clubs2 = \u2192 [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] (loan)\n| caps2 = 14\n| goals2 = 1\n| years3 = 2018\u20132020\n| clubs3 = [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]]\n| caps3 = 24\n| goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2019\u20132020\n| clubs4 = \u2192 [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] (loan)\n| caps4 = 18\n| goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2020\u2013\n| clubs5 = [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]]\n| caps5 = 0\n| goals5 = 0\n| club-update = 22:26, 31 January 2020 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Matthew Thomas Palmer''' (born 27 February 1995) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[EFL League Two|League Two]] club [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]].\n\n==Career==\n===Burton Albion===\nPalmer was born in [[Derby]], Derbyshire.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.11v11.com/players/matty-palmer-239715/ |title=Matty Palmer |website=11v11.com |publisher=AFS Enterprises |accessdate=1 August 2018}}</ref> He joined [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]]'s youth academy after being released by [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]].<ref name=BurtonProfile>{{cite web |url=http://www.burtonalbionfc.co.uk/team/player-profile/index.aspx?playerid=493306&tcmuri=310436 |title=Burton Albion FC player profiles: Matthew Palmer |publisher=Burton Albion F.C. |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224225245/http://www.burtonalbionfc.co.uk/team/player-profile/index.aspx?playerid=493306&tcmuri=310436 |archivedate=24 December 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> He secured the award for most improved young player at the end of his first season as a scholar at the club.<ref name=BurtonProfile/> He made his debut on 15 November 2012 as an 89th-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in the [[FA Cup]], in a 2\u20130 away win over [[Altrincham F.C.|Altrincham]].<ref name=sb1213/> He made his [[EFL League Two|League Two]] debut on 5 April 2013, coming on 79 minutes into a 7\u20131 away defeat to [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]].<ref name=sb1213/> Palmer's first goal came on 10 November 2013 in a 2\u20130 home win over [[Hereford United F.C.|Hereford United]] in the first round of the FA Cup.<ref name=sb1314/> He came on as a 78th-minute substitute on 26 May in the [[2014 Football League Two play-off Final|2014 League Two play-off Final]], in which Burton were beaten 1\u20130 by [[Fleetwood Town F.C.|Fleetwood Town]] at [[Wembley Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/27465323 |title=Burton Albion 0\u20131 Fleetwood Town |first=Phil |last=Maiden |publisher=BBC Sport |date=26 May 2014 |accessdate=1 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nPalmer joined [[EFL League One|League One]] club [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] on 22 January 2016 on a one-month [[Loan (sports)|loan]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.oldhamathletic.co.uk/news/2016/january/incoming-palmer-signs-on-loan/ |title=Incoming: Palmer signs on loan |publisher=Oldham Athletic A.F.C. |date=22 January 2016 |accessdate=1 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Rotherham United===\nPalmer signed for League One club [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]] on 25 January 2018 on a two-and-a-half-year contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/rotherham-united/rotherham-united-midfielder-matt-palmer-joins-millers-1-8980739 |title=Rotherham United: Midfielder Matt Palmer joins Millers |first=Paul |last=Davis |newspaper=The Star |location=Sheffield |date=25 January 2018 |accessdate=1 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe joined newly relegated League Two club [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] on 5 July 2019 on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk/news/2019/july/palmer-pens-season-long-loan-switch/ |title=Palmer pens season-long loan switch |publisher=Bradford City A.F.C. |date=5 July 2019 |accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Swindon Town===\nPalmer signed for club [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]] on 31 January 2020 on an 18-month deal after his contract was terminated at [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51335088 |title=Swindon Town: Matt Palmer leaves Rotherham following recall from loan at Bradford |publisher=BBC Sport |date=31 January 2020 |accessdate=31 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|<!--match played-->18 January 2020}}\n\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|[[FA Cup]]\n!colspan=2|[[EFL Cup|League Cup]]\n!colspan=2|Other\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=7|[[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]]\n|[[2012\u201313 Burton Albion F.C. season|2012\u201313]]<ref name=sb1213>{{soccerbase season|66698|2012|name=Matty Palmer|accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n|[[EFL League Two|League Two]]\n|2||0||1||0||0||0||0||0||3||0\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Burton Albion F.C. season|2013\u201314]]<ref name=sb1314>{{soccerbase season|66698|2013|name=Matty Palmer|accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n|League Two\n|40||0||3||1||2||0||3{{efn|One appearance in [[Football League Trophy]], two in [[EFL League Two play-offs|League Two play-offs]]}}||0||48||1\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 Burton Albion F.C. season|2014\u201315]]<ref name=sb1415>{{soccerbase season|66698|2014|name=Matty Palmer|accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n|League Two\n|33||4||1||0||2||0||1{{efn|name=FLT|Appearance in Football League Trophy}}||0||37||4\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 Burton Albion F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref name=sb1516>{{soccerbase season|66698|2015|name=Matty Palmer|accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n|[[EFL League One|League One]]\n|14||0||1||0||2||1||1{{efn|name=FLT}}||0||18||1\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Burton Albion F.C. season|2016\u201317]]<ref name=sb1617>{{soccerbase season|66698|2016|name=Matty Palmer|accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n|[[EFL Championship|Championship]]\n|36||1||1||0||2||0||colspan=2|\u2014||39||1\n|-\n|[[2017\u201318 Burton Albion F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=sb1718/>\n|Championship\n|11||1||0||0||3||0||colspan=2|\u2014||14||1\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!136||6||7||1||11||1||5||0||159||8\n|-\n|[[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] (loan)\n|[[2015\u201316 Oldham Athletic A.F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref name=sb1516/>\n|League One\n|14||1||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||14||1\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]]\n|[[2017\u201318 Rotherham United F.C. season|2017\u201318]]<ref name=sb1718>{{soccerbase season|66698|2017|name=Matty Palmer|accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n|League One\n|14||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||2{{efn|Appearances in [[EFL League One play-offs|League One play-offs]]}}||0||16||0\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 Rotherham United F.C. season|2018\u201319]]<ref name=sb1819>{{soccerbase season|66698|2018|name=Matty Palmer|accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n|Championship\n|10||0||1||0||2||0||colspan=2|\u2014||13||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!24||0||1||0||2||0||2||0||29||0\n|-\n|[[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] (loan)\n|[[2019\u201320 Bradford City A.F.C. season|2019\u201320]]<ref name=sb1920>{{soccerbase season|66698|2019|accessdate=31 January 2020}}</ref>\n|League Two\n|18||0||0||0||0||0||0||0||18||0\n|-\n!colspan=3|Career total\n!192||7||8||1||13||1||7||0||220||9\n|}\n\n{{notelist}}\n\n==Honours==\n'''Burton Albion'''\n*[[Football League Two]]: [[2014\u201315 Football League Two|2014\u201315]]<ref>{{cite book |editor-first=John |editor-last=Anderson |title=Sky Sports Football Yearbook 2015\u20132016 |year=2015 |publisher=Headline Publishing Group |location=London |isbn=978-1-4722-2416-3 |pages=94\u201395}}</ref>\n*[[Football League One]] runner-up: [[2015\u201316 Football League One|2015\u201316]]<ref>{{cite book |editor-first=John |editor-last=Anderson |title=Sky Sports Football Yearbook 2016\u20132017 |year=2016 |publisher=Headline Publishing Group |location=London |isbn=978-1-4722-3395-0 |pages=98\u201399}}</ref>\n\n'''Rotherham United'''\n*[[EFL League One play-offs]]: [[2018 English Football League play-offs#League One|2018]]<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44186999 |title=Rotherham United 2\u20131 Shrewsbury Town |first=Ged |last=Scott |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 May 2018 |accessdate=27 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://www.themillers.co.uk/teams/first-team/midfielder/matthew-palmer/ Profile] at the Rotherham United F.C. website\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Palmer, Matt}}\n[[Category:1995 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Derby]]\n[[Category:Footballers from Derbyshire]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Derby County F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Burton Albion F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Oldham Athletic A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Rotherham United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bradford City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2018}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Matt Palmer\n| image = \n| image_size = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Matthew Thomas Palmer<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.football-league.co.uk/staticFiles/4e/bd/0,,10794~179534,00.pdf |title=Professional retain list & free transfers: 2012/13 |publisher=The Football League |format=PDF |page=57 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140802074454/http://www.football-league.co.uk/staticFiles/4e/bd/0%2C%2C10794~179534%2C00.pdf |archivedate=2 August 2014 |url-status=dead}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1995|2|27|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/players/matthew-palmer/257972/ |title=M. Palmer: Summary |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Derby]], England\n| height = {{convert|1.79|m|order=flip}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.themillers.co.uk/teams/first-team/midfielder/matthew-palmer/ |title=Matthew Palmer |publisher=Rotherham United F.C. |accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n| position = [[Midfielder]]<ref>{{Hugman|24871|accessdate=1 August 2018}}</ref>\n| currentclub = [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]]\n| clubnumber = 8\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]]\n| youthyears2 = {{0|000}}\u20132012\n| youthclubs2 = [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]]\n| years1 = 2012\u20132018\n| clubs1 = [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]]\n| caps1 = 136\n| goals1 = 6\n| years2 = 2016\n| clubs2 = \u2192 [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] (loan)\n| caps2 = 14\n| goals2 = 1\n| years3 = 2018\u20132020\n| clubs3 = [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]]\n| caps3 = 24\n| goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2019\u20132020\n| clubs4 = \u2192 [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] (loan)\n| caps4 = 18\n| goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2020\u2013\n| clubs5 = [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]]\n| caps5 = 0\n| goals5 = 0\n| club-update = 22:26, 31 January 2020 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Matthew Thomas Palmer''' (born 27 February 1995) is an English professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[EFL League Two|League Two]] club [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]].\n\n==Career==\n===Burton Albion===\nPalmer was born in [[Derby]], Derbyshire.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.11v11.com/players/matty-palmer-239715/ |title=Matty Palmer |website=11v11.com |publisher=AFS Enterprises |accessdate=1 August 2018}}</ref> He joined [[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]]'s youth academy after being released by [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]].<ref name=BurtonProfile>{{cite web |url=http://www.burtonalbionfc.co.uk/team/player-profile/index.aspx?playerid=493306&tcmuri=310436 |title=Burton Albion FC player profiles: Matthew Palmer |publisher=Burton Albion F.C. |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131224225245/http://www.burtonalbionfc.co.uk/team/player-profile/index.aspx?playerid=493306&tcmuri=310436 |archivedate=24 December 2013 |url-status=dead}}</ref> He secured the award for most improved young player at the end of his first season as a scholar at the club.<ref name=BurtonProfile/> He made his debut on 15 November 2012 as an 89th-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in the [[FA Cup]], in a 2\u20130 away win over [[Altrincham F.C.|Altrincham]].<ref name=sb1213/> He made his [[EFL League Two|League Two]] debut on 5 April 2013, coming on 79 minutes into a 7\u20131 away defeat to [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]].<ref name=sb1213/> Palmer's first goal came on 10 November 2013 in a 2\u20130 home win over [[Hereford United F.C.|Hereford United]] in the first round of the FA Cup.<ref name=sb1314/> He came on as a 78th-minute substitute on 26 May in the [[2014 Football League Two play-off Final|2014 League Two play-off Final]], in which Burton were beaten 1\u20130 by [[Fleetwood Town F.C.|Fleetwood Town]] at [[Wembley Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/27465323 |title=Burton Albion 0\u20131 Fleetwood Town |first=Phil |last=Maiden |publisher=BBC Sport |date=26 May 2014 |accessdate=1 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nPalmer joined [[EFL League One|League One]] club [[Oldham Athletic A.F.C.|Oldham Athletic]] on 22 January 2016 on a one-month [[Loan (sports)|loan]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.oldhamathletic.co.uk/news/2016/january/incoming-palmer-signs-on-loan/ |title=Incoming: Palmer signs on loan |publisher=Oldham Athletic A.F.C. |date=22 January 2016 |accessdate=1 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Rotherham United===\nPalmer signed for League One club [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]] on 25 January 2018 on a two-and-a-half-year contract for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/rotherham-united/rotherham-united-midfielder-matt-palmer-joins-millers-1-8980739 |title=Rotherham United: Midfielder Matt Palmer joins Millers |first=Paul |last=Davis |newspaper=The Star |location=Sheffield |date=25 January 2018 |accessdate=1 August 2018}}</ref>\n\nHe joined newly relegated League Two club [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] on 5 July 2019 on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bradfordcityfc.co.uk/news/2019/july/palmer-pens-season-long-loan-switch/ |title=Palmer pens season-long loan switch |publisher=Bradford City A.F.C. |date=5 July 2019 |accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Swindon Town===\nPalmer signed for club [[Swindon Town F.C.|Swindon Town]] on 31 January 2020 on an 18-month deal after his contract was terminated at [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51335088 |title=Swindon Town: Matt Palmer leaves Rotherham following recall from loan at Bradford |publisher=BBC Sport |date=31 January 2020 |accessdate=31 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{{updated|<!--match played-->18 January 2020}}\n\n{| class=wikitable style=text-align:center\n|+ Appearances and goals by club, season and competition\n|-\n!rowspan=2|Club\n!rowspan=2|Season\n!colspan=3|League\n!colspan=2|[[FA Cup]]\n!colspan=2|[[EFL Cup|League Cup]]\n!colspan=2|Other\n!colspan=2|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=7|[[Burton Albion F.C.|Burton Albion]]\n|[[2012\u201313 Burton Albion F.C. season|2012\u201313]]<ref name=sb1213>{{soccerbase season|66698|2012|name=Matty Palmer|accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n|[[EFL League Two|League Two]]\n|2||0||1||0||0||0||0||0||3||0\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 Burton Albion F.C. season|2013\u201314]]<ref name=sb1314>{{soccerbase season|66698|2013|name=Matty Palmer|accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n|League Two\n|40||0||3||1||2||0||3{{efn|One appearance in [[Football League Trophy]], two in [[EFL League Two play-offs|League Two play-offs]]}}||0||48||1\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 Burton Albion F.C. season|2014\u201315]]<ref name=sb1415>{{soccerbase season|66698|2014|name=Matty Palmer|accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n|League Two\n|33||4||1||0||2||0||1{{efn|name=FLT|Appearance in Football League Trophy}}||0||37||4\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 Burton Albion F.C. season|2015\u201316]]<ref name=sb1516>{{soccerbase season|66698|2015|name=Matty Palmer|accessdate=6 July 2019}}</ref>\n|[[EFL League One|League One]]\n|14||0||1||0||2||1||1{{efn|name=FLT}}||0||18||1\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 Burton Albion F.C. season|2016\u201317]]<ref name=sb1617>{{soc